<p>
  As the organization that encompasses over fifteen YMCA branches across Arizona, Valley of the Sun YMCA needed a website that highlighted all of their available activities, membership options, and community efforts. Our team at BIG YAM created a site that allowed users to quickly see available activities at their nearest branch, sign up for and manage their family's activities, and keep track of their branch's latest announcements.
</p>

<p>
  This was project was created during my time at BIG YAM, The Parsons Agency. As a front-end developer, my contributions included:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    Collaborating with designers to code static HTML, CSS, and JavaScript based on their designs in Adobe Photoshop
  </li>
  
  <li>
    Focusing on a mobile-first implementation and working through extensive iterations to ensure the site was fluid and responsive
  </li>
  
  <li>
    Working closely with back-end developers on building a custom WordPress theme and CMS integration
  </li>
  
  <li>
    Ensuring the design adapts to multiple languages and accessibility options to adjust the text size
  </li>
  
  <li>
    Styling the third-party scheduling integration to make it cohesive with the rest of the site's design
  </li>
  
  <li>Implementing CSS animations, as well as custom select dropdowns and stylized scrollbars</li>
</ul>

